subSubSection.paragraph:
BIOLOGY: Several species were reared from various dipterous hosts (
Muesebeck, 1980
); the most frequently attacked families include the fruit flies (
Tephritidae
), hereby demonstrating the importance in biocontrol (
Loiácono, 1981
; 
Silvestri, 1914
). Species are encountered in a multitude of habitats, from lowlands to highlands. Several species were collected in light traps in 
Brazil
but none associated with ants.
